<servinfosub id = "AENAP70AA504019003">
<title>
DTC Confirmation Procedure
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set steering wheel in straight-ahead position.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Repeat Step 2) and 3) several times.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70AA504019004">
<title>
DTC Troubleshooting
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
This DTC might be detected when battery is run down or the voltage is very low.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
If ignition is set “OFF” with force applied to steering wheel, there may be a case that B1162 is detected because steering lock unit cannot be unlocked. This is a temporary malfunction and not a permanent defect.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<diag type = "test" id = "AENAP70AA504019005">
<testgroup id = "AENAP70AA504019006">
<title>
Battery voltage check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Make sure that battery terminal voltage is 11 V or higher.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is it in good condition?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 2.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Check battery and generator.
</ptxt>
</item>
<list2 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Battery: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A1A04001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Generator: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A1A04003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list2>
</list1>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70AA504019007">
<title>
DTC check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70AA504003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is current DTC B1162 detected, not history?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 4.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 3.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70AA504019008">
<title>
DTC recheck
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Clear DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70AA504004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set steering wheel in straight-ahead position.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Open driver door.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Perform 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70AA504019003">DTC Confirmation Procedure</intxref>
 and then recheck DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70AA504003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is current DTC B1162 detected?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 4.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
End. (Intermittent trouble.)
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70AA504019009">
<title>
Steering lock unit operation check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Open driver door.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Confirm that ignition is “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Repeat Step 2) and 3) several times.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that steering lock does lock / unlock according to change of ignition.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is it in good condition?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
End. (Intermittent trouble.)
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 5.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70AA504019010">
<title>
Steering lock unit power supply circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect steering lock unit connector.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check for proper terminal connection to steering lock unit connector.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
If connections are OK, check the following points.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Voltage between “A1” and “C2” is battery voltage when ignition is switched from “OFF” to “ON”.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Voltage between “A2” and “C1” is battery voltage when ignition is switched from “OFF” to “ON”.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</test1>
<question>
Are they in good condition?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Clear DTC, and then Go to Step 8. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70AA504004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Clear DTC, and then Go to Step 6. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70AA504004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70AA504019011">
<title>
Steering lock unit ground circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that voltage between each of “A1” and “A2” circuit and ground is battery voltage when ignition is switched from “OFF” to “ON”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is it in good condition?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Repair or replace “C1” and “C2” circuits.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 7.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70AA504019012">
<title>
Steering lock unit power supply circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect “G28” connector.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check for proper terminal connection to “G28” connector.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
If connections are OK, check the following points.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Resistance of “A1” and “A2” circuits: less than 3 Ω
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Resistance between each of “A1” and “A2” circuits and ground: infinity
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Resistance between each of “A1” and “A2” circuit terminal and each terminal at steering lock unit connector: infinity
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Voltage of “A1” and “A2” circuits: 0 – 1 V (when ignition is “ON”)
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</test1>
<question>
Are they in good condition?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Replace keyless start control module and recheck DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70AA506003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Repair or replace defective wire harness.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70AA504019013">
<title>
DTC check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Replace steering lock unit. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A6206014"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Open driver door.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Perform 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70AA504019003">DTC Confirmation Procedure</intxref>
 and then recheck DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70AA504003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is DTC B1162 still detected?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Replace keyless start control module and recheck DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70AA506003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
End. (Steering lock unit was faulty.)
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
</diag>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
